1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Stop it.

2
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Stop what?

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,000
You're talking about me and Morse code.

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,000
But you know what?

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Joke's on you because I know Morse code.

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Ha!

7
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Yeah, that's what we're doing.

8
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:28,000
In our very limited free time and with our very limited budget, we went and got a nanny,

9
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:32,000
and then we went out and took a class on a very outmoded and very unnecessary form of communication

10
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,000
just so we could talk about you in front of you.

11
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Yep, that's exactly what we did.

12
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:42,000
It all started when Dwight was tapping his foot against the leg of his desk.

13
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:48,000
When I asked him to stop, he said, I will, when you lose the baby weight.

14
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:53,000
Very well. I must have imagined it. I apologize.

15
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Detonator. Detonator, where? Michael!

16
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Jim, are you clicking a detonator?

17
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,000
It's a pin. He said there's a detonator in here.

18
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,000
Okay.

19
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Michael, that is totally not...

20
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:27,000
True.

21
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Right?

22
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,000
Yep.

23
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Wait, he just coughed not in Morse code, so he said that's not not true.

24
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,000
That's a double negative.

25
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:37,000
The only Morse code I know is J Morse code. ABF. Always be funny.

26
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,000
Michael, come on.

27
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Get back to work, Dwight. Please.

28
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:47,000
Fine.

29
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Hey, tap away.
